Writes the text to the system's std err, but does not automatically add a newline at the end. Unlike console(), this does not use anything else to format the output, though in many cases they will behave the same. Unlike other print methdods, colors and other formatting characters WILL "bleed" through, so print_err(color(RED) . 'This is red') will also cause the next line to also be red, so if you need to print multiple lines out, you should manually reset the color with print_out(color(RESET)), or use sys_err.
